---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Cycling Injuries"
	heroSubtitle="Cycling injuries are common — especially when your position, strength or training load isn't quite right. Get back on the bike pain free."
	breadcrumb="Cycling Injuries"
	seoTitle="Cycling Injuries Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Expert cycling injury treatment in Clapham, London. We address root causes — bike setup, strength and training load — to get you riding pain free."
	intro={[
		"Cycling injuries are common — especially when your position on the bike, strength and conditioning regime or training load isn't quite right. We focus on understanding root causes rather than just addressing symptoms.",
		"Whether it's knee pain, a niggling back or numbness in the hands, we'll look at how you move, how you load the bike and how you train, and build a plan to get you riding pain free.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get it"
	symptomsHighlight="checked"
	symptomsIntro="It's worth coming in for an assessment if you're experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"Pain at the front of the knee, especially during longer rides",
		"Lower back stiffness that builds while riding",
		"Neck or shoulder tension on longer sessions",
		"Numbness or tingling in the hands or feet",
		"Pain on the outside of the hip",
		"Discomfort or irritation when sitting on the saddle",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we treat"
	treatmentHighlight="cycling injuries"
	treatmentIntro="Your treatment plan is built around your specific presentation and may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy to improve strength and control",
		"Manual therapy and stretching to reduce stiffness",
		"Rehab exercises tailored to riding demands",
		"Advice on bike setup, cleats, and positioning",
		"Guidance on training load and return to riding",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Road cyclists and club riders",
		"Commuters dealing with daily-ride niggles",
		"Triathletes managing bike-specific issues",
		"Mountain bikers with overload or impact injuries",
		"Cyclists returning after injury or surgery",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "Why do I only get pain when cycling?", a: "Often it\\'s related to your bike set-up or position rather than the joint itself. Small adjustments can make a big difference." },
		{ q: "Can a bike fit help with back or knee pain?", a: "Yes — your position on the bike plays a big role in how your body loads during cycling." },
		{ q: "What are the most common cycling injuries?", a: "Knee pain, lower back pain, and hand or foot numbness are among the most common." },
		{ q: "Can I keep riding while I recover?", a: "In many cases, yes. We\\'ll guide you on what to modify and when it\\'s safe to push harder." },
	]}
/>
